Agile vs. Waterfall

Waterfall is planned-out from the beginning: risks starting over at beginning
Agile is based on "sprints"
scrum vs. scrum master
standup meetings: did yesterday, doing today, going to do tomorrow
controlling scope creep

Waterfall doesn't allow for much client involvement

